<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="comments">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
Because the type specimen of 
<taxonomicName class="Pucciniomycetes" genus="Uredo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Uredo mildbraedii" order="Pucciniales" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="mildbraedii">Uredo mildbraedii</taxonomicName>
lacked teliospores, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ritschel, A" journalOrPublisher="Bibliotheca Mycologica" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 132" title="Monograph of the genus Hemileia (Uredinales)." volume="200" year="2005">Ritschel (2005)</bibRefCitation>
described a new species, 
<taxonomicName class="Pucciniomycetes" genus="Hemileia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hemileia sydowiorum" order="Pucciniales" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="sydowiorum">Hemileia sydowiorum</taxonomicName>
, using a type specimen having teliospores. With the new ICN, 
<taxonomicName class="Pucciniomycetes" genus="Uredo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Uredo mildbraedii" order="Pucciniales" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="mildbraedii">Uredo mildbraedii</taxonomicName>
provides the epithet of priority for this species. The name 
<taxonomicName class="Pucciniomycetes" genus="Hemileia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hemileia pavetticola" order="Pucciniales" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="pavetticola">Hemileia pavetticola</taxonomicName>
Roger was published without a Latin diagnosis. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ritschel, A" journalOrPublisher="Bibliotheca Mycologica" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" pagination="1 - 132" title="Monograph of the genus Hemileia (Uredinales)." volume="200" year="2005">Ritschel (2005)</bibRefCitation>
lists 1914 as the year of publication for the name 
<taxonomicName class="Pucciniomycetes" genus="Uredo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Uredo mildbraedii" order="Pucciniales" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="mildbraedii">Uredo mildbraedii</taxonomicName>
, while, in fact, this name was published earlier in the account of the first expedition that appeared in 1911.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
